.TH "gmap_idte_one" 9 "gmap_idte_one" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gmap_idte_one \- invalidate a single region or segment table entry
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" gmap_idte_one
.BI "(unsigned long asce "  ","
.BI "unsigned long vaddr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "asce" 12
region or segment table *origin* + table-type bits
.IP "vaddr" 12
virtual address to identify the table entry to flush
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The invalid bit of a single region or segment table entry is set
and the associated TLB entries depending on the entry are flushed.
The table-type of the \fIasce\fP identifies the portion of the \fIvaddr\fP
that is used as the invalidation index.
